12  class KSComponentMath :
13  public KSComponent

15  public:
16  KSComponentMath( std::vector< KSComponent* > aParentComponents, std::vector< XValueType* > aParentPointers, std::string aTerm ) :
17  KSComponent(),
18  fParentComponents( aParentComponents ),
19  fParents( aParentPointers ),
20  fResult( KSNumerical< XValueType >::Zero() )
21  {
22  Set( &fResult );
23  this->SetParent( aParentComponents.at( 0 ) );
24  for( size_t tIndex = 0; tIndex < aParentComponents.size(); tIndex++ )
25  {
26  aParentComponents.at( tIndex )->AddChild( this );
27  }
28 
29  for( size_t tIndex = 0; tIndex < fParents.size(); tIndex++ )
30  {
31  //create std::string for variable name x0,x1,etc.
32  std::string tVariable( "x" );
33  std::stringstream tIndexConverter;
34  tIndexConverter << tIndex;
35  tVariable += tIndexConverter.str();
36 
37  std::stringstream tParameterConverter;
38  tParameterConverter << "[" << tIndexConverter.str() << "]";
39 
40  //replace x with [index], this denotes a parameter for TF1
41  while( aTerm.find( tVariable ) != std::string::npos )
42  {
43  aTerm.replace( aTerm.find( tVariable ), tVariable.length(), tParameterConverter.str() );
44  }
45  }
46 
47  fTerm = aTerm;
48 
49  //check if all x are replaced in formula
50  if( fTerm.find( std::string( "x" ) ) != std::string::npos || fTerm.find( std::string( "X" ) ) != std::string::npos )
51  {
52  objctmsg( eError ) << "Error in KSComponentMath: could not replace all variables in term! Use only x0,x1,etc., one for each component" << eom;
53  }
54 
55  // initialize function once, parameters are updated every PushUpdate call
56  fFunction = new TF1( "(anonymous)", fTerm.c_str(), -1., 1. );
57  }
58  KSComponentMath( const KSComponentMath< XValueType >& aCopy ) :
59  KSComponent( aCopy ),
60  fParentComponents( aCopy.fParentComponents ),
61  fParents( aCopy.fParents ),
62  fResult( aCopy.fResult ),
63  fTerm( aCopy.fTerm ),
64  fFunction( aCopy.fFunction )
65  {
66  Set( &fResult );
67  this->SetParent( aCopy.fParentComponent );
68  for( size_t tIndex = 0; tIndex < aCopy.fParentComponents.size(); tIndex++ )
69  {
70  aCopy.fParentComponents.at( tIndex )->AddChild( this );
71  }
72  }

74  {

91  if( tComponent == NULL )

107  void PushUpdateComponent()
108  {
109  objctmsg_debug( "component math <" << this->GetName() << "> pushing update" << eom );
110 
111  for( size_t tIndex = 0; tIndex < fParents.size(); tIndex++ )
112  {
113  fParentComponents.at( tIndex )->PullUpdate();
114  fFunction->SetParameter(tIndex, *(fParents.at(tIndex)));
115  }
116 
117  fResult = fFunction->Eval( 0 );
118  return;
119  }
